"```sql\nSELECT COUNT(*)\nFROM client\nJOIN disp ON client.client_id = disp.client_id\nJOIN account ON disp.account_id = account.account_id\nJOIN district ON account.district_id = district.district_id\nWHERE district.A2 = 'Jesenik' AND client.gender = 'F';\n```\n\nThis SQL query counts the number of female clients (gender = 'F') who have opened their accounts in the Jesenik branch. It joins the `client`, `disp`, `account`, and `district` tables using the appropriate foreign key relationships and filters the results based on the district name and gender."